    "title": {
      "rendered": "10 e-Newsletter Best Practices for Nonprofits"
    },
    "content": {
      "rendered": "<p><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/news-blog-image.gif\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-16694\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/news-blog-image-300x300.gif?resize=300%2C300\" alt=\"news-blog-image\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/news-blog-image.gif?resize=300%2C300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/news-blog-image.gif?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/news-blog-image.gif?resize=200%2C200&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/news-blog-image.gif?resize=75%2C75&amp;ssl=1 75w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a>Despite the rapid rise of social media, more online donations are made from a <a href=\"https://econsultancy.com/blog/64614-email-remains-the-best-digital-channel-for-roi#i.1rpoywozarf0mr\">click in an e-newsletter than any other source</a>. In fact,\u00a0in 2013\u00a0for every 1,000 fundraising messages delivered, <a href=\"http://www.mrbenchmarks.com/\">nonprofits raised $17</a>. That was a 21% decrease from the previous year, but the decrease is mostly likely due to <a href=\"http://www.nptechforgood.com/2014/08/24/10-online-fundraising-best-practices-for-nonprofits/\">poor online fundraising practices</a>, such as not having a mobile-optimized donate page and e-newsletter design.</p>\n<p>Furthermore,\u00a0<a href=\"http://pewinternet.org/Reports/2012/Older-adults-and-internet-use/Main-Report/Online-activities.aspx\">email still dominates</a> among online adults\u00a0of all ages and thanks to the rise of social media, e-newsletter growth in the nonprofit sector grew 14% in 2013, especially for small nonprofits. Thus, not only is the myth that social media replaces email false, but now it is also understood and proven that email use is increased by social media and that in fact the two tools are complimentary and increase the success of your online fundraising campaigns. With\u00a0that said, below are 10 e-newsletter best practices that can help your nonprofit raise more funds online:</p>\n<h2>1. Prioritize mobile design.</h2>\n<p><a href=\"http://marketingland.com/34-percent-email-opens-now-happen-pc-83277\">66% of emails</a> are now opened either on a smartphone or tablet. For email to continue to be effective in your content and fundraising strategies, your nonprofit must <a href=\"http://www.nptechforgood.com/2014/02/17/3-mobile-compatible-nonprofit-e-newsletters-to-subscribe-to-and-learn-from/\">prioritize mobile design</a>.</p>\n<table border=\"0\" width=\"600\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"center\"><a href=\"http://www.wildlifealliance.org/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/wildlife-alliance-e-newsletter-11.png?resize=195%2C293\" alt=\"\" width=\"195\" height=\"293\" /></a></td>\n<td align=\"center\"><a href=\"http://www.wildlifealliance.org/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/wildlife-alliance-e-newsletter-21.png?resize=195%2C293\" alt=\"\" width=\"195\" height=\"293\" /></a></td>\n<td align=\"center\"><a href=\"http://www.wildlifealliance.org/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/wildlife-alliance-e-newsletter-3.png?resize=195%2C293\" alt=\"\" width=\"195\" height=\"293\" /></a></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h2>2. Limit stories and calls-to-action to five or less and\u00a0keep text to a minimum.</h2>\n<p>The purpose of an e-newsletter is no longer to provide a lot of news, but rather to regularly remind your supporters that your nonprofit is doing good work and to inspire them to get involved.\u00a0Focus on 1-5 stories and/or calls-to-action and keep text to a minimum. People don&#8217;t read online like they used to and too much text is overwhelming. In addition, convert call-to-action links into call-to-action buttons for easy tapping on mobile devices.</p>\n<table border=\"0\" width=\"600\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"center\"><a href=\"http://water.org/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/water1.png?resize=195%2C293\" alt=\"\" width=\"195\" height=\"293\" border=\"1\" /></a></td>\n<td align=\"center\"><a href=\"http://water.org/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/water2.png?resize=195%2C293\" alt=\"\" width=\"195\" height=\"293\" border=\"1\" /></a></td>\n<td align=\"center\"><a href=\"http://water.org/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/water3.png?resize=195%2C293\" alt=\"\" width=\"195\" height=\"293\" border=\"1\" /></a></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h2>3. Integrate a &#8220;Donate&#8221; button and social networking icons.</h2>\n<p>A\u00a0&#8220;donate&#8221; button and social networking icons should be placed\u00a0at the top of your e-newsletter template design because many readers will not scroll to the bottom of your e-newsletter.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.hrw.org/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-16672\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/human-rights-watch-enews.png?resize=600%2C283\" alt=\"human rights watch enews\" width=\"600\" height=\"283\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/human-rights-watch-enews.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/human-rights-watch-enews.png?resize=300%2C141&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2>4. Enable social sharing.</h2>\n<p>Hosted e-newsletter services allow subscribers to share your entire e-newsletter to their social networks, but allowing subscribers to share individual articles is smart strategy.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.hrw.org/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-16674\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/hrw2.png?resize=600%2C250\" alt=\"hrw2\" width=\"600\" height=\"250\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/hrw2.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/hrw2.png?resize=300%2C125&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2>5. Add screenshots of video.</h2>\n<p>E-newsletters that include video have <a href=\"http://www.flimp.net/blog/video-emails-generate-click-through-rate-7x-the-email-industry-average/\">double the click-through rate</a>. You can link the video screenshot directly to YouTube or Instagram or to the videos embedded directly inside your website or blog. In the <a href=\"http://www.ifaw.org/united-states\">IFAW</a> e-newsletter below, the video was strategically\u00a0linked to a donate page where subscribers could watch the video.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.ifaw.org/united-states\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-16676\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/IFAW-email.png?resize=600%2C326\" alt=\"IFAW email\" width=\"600\" height=\"326\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/IFAW-email.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/IFAW-email.png?resize=300%2C163&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2>6. Experiment with sending your e-newsletter more often.</h2>\n<p>Nonprofits send out an average of <a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/nonprofitorgs/8613983476/in/photostream\">3.8 e-newsletters per month</a>, however most small and\u00a0medium-sized nonprofits only send out e-newsletters monthly or quarterly. As you can see in the stats below, 40,000 e-newsletter subscribers drive more traffic to this blog than one million social network followers. Red dots are days that e-newsletters have been sent:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/stats.png\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-16678\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/stats.png?resize=600%2C233\" alt=\"stats\" width=\"600\" height=\"233\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/stats.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/stats.png?resize=300%2C116&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2>7. Keep subject lines short.</h2>\n<p>Short subject lines that easily can be read on smartphones and tablets result in the highest open rates. Thus, limit your subject lines to 50 characters or less.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.worldwildlife.org/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-16681\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/wwf-email.png?resize=600%2C398\" alt=\"wwf email\" width=\"600\" height=\"398\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/wwf-email.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/wwf-email.png?resize=300%2C199&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2>8. Add e-newsletter opt-ins to every page of your website and blog.</h2>\n<p>Nonprofits now regularly share links to articles and blog posts hosted on\u00a0their website on social networks, so to covert followers into e-newsletter subscribers, add e-newsletter opt-ins to <a href=\"http://www.projectaware.org/\">every page of your website</a> and blog.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.projectaware.org/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-16683\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/project-aware-one.png?resize=600%2C376\" alt=\"project aware one\" width=\"600\" height=\"376\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/project-aware-one.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/project-aware-one.png?resize=300%2C188&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.projectaware.org/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-16684\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/project-aware-two.png?resize=600%2C367\" alt=\"project aware two\" width=\"600\" height=\"367\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/project-aware-two.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/project-aware-two.png?resize=300%2C183&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2>9. Create &#8220;Subscribe&#8221; graphics to promote on social networks.</h2>\n<p>Text-based calls-to-subscribe no longer work. You must created compelling visuals for all calls-to-action posted on social networks.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.rainforesttrust.org/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-16686\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/rainforest.png?resize=600%2C388\" alt=\"rainforest\" width=\"600\" height=\"388\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/rainforest.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/rainforest.png?resize=300%2C194&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.plunket.org.nz/\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-16687\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/plunket.png?resize=600%2C374\" alt=\"plunket\" width=\"600\" height=\"374\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/plunket.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/plunket.png?resize=300%2C187&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2>10. Never, ever send e-newsletters BCC\u00a0with attached PDFs.</h2>\n<p>While cutting edge in 1990&#8217;s, BCC emails with PDFs attached are a huge faux paux in online marketing. Besides being annoying to the recipients, it will also get your nonprofit classified as a spammer and most of those emails will go into Spam folders or be blocked completely.\u00a0Yet, in 2014 this is still a common practice especially with small nonprofits most likely because they do not want to invest in a hosted email service. However, BCC emails are hampering your fundraising efforts, hurting your brand, and in most cases pointless since so few of these emails are opened. Investing is a <a href=\"http://email-marketing-service-review.toptenreviews.com/\">hosted email service</a> is an absolute must.</p>\n<hr />\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 17px;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; font-weight: bold;\"><em>Mobile for Good: A How-To Fundraising Guide for Nonprofits</em></span></span></strong></h2>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Mobile-Good-How--Fundraising-Nonprofits/dp/0071825460\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignleft wp-image-16024\" style=\"margin: 10px; border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/mobile-for-good-look-inside.jpg?resize=99%2C150\" alt=\"mobile for good look inside\" width=\"99\" height=\"150\" /></a>Based on more than 20 years of experience and 25,000+ hours spent utilizing mobile and social media, <a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Mobile-Good-How--Fundraising-Nonprofits/dp/0071825460\"><em><strong>Mobile for Good: A How-To Fundraising Guide for Nonprofits</strong></em></a> is a comprehensive 256-page book packed with more than 500 best practices. Written on the premise that all communications and fundraising are now mobile and social, Mobile for Good is a step-by-step how-to guide for writing, implementing, and maintaining a mobile and social fundraising strategy for your nonprofit.</p>\n",
